<subSubSection pageId="16" pageNumber="17" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="16.[151,1437,151,564]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,320,151,177]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Remarks.</emphasis>
Three of the twelve females included in the vial n° 
<collectionCode LSID="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34988" box="[983,1073,152,178]" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34988" name="Museum National d'Histoire Naturelle" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">MNHN</collectionCode>
<collectionCode box="[1085,1126,152,178]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">AR</collectionCode>
<number box="[1139,1198,152,178]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="9167.0">9167</number>
(“Alpes, Pyrénées- Orientales” and “Tré-La-Tête (
<date box="[527,655,190,216]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="1913-08">
août 
<number box="[589,655,190,216]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="1913.0">1913</number>
</date>
)”, also labelled “ 
<taxonomicName box="[865,1099,191,216]" class="Arachnida" family="Gnaphosidae" genus="Drassodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="prolixus">
<emphasis box="[865,1099,191,216]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Drassodes prolixus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
”, not described by Simon), show slight differences in the shape of the epigynal atrium which is subcircular (
<figureCitation box="[1102,1187,229,255]" captionStart="FIGURES 10 – 19. 10 – 15" captionStartId="12.[151,269,1802,1826]" captionTargetBox="[171,1414,182,1782]" captionTargetId="figure@12.[160,1427,174,1786]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 10 – 19. 10 – 15 Drassodex heeri (Pavesi, 1873) (10 – 13 SMF 22517 / 3; 14 – 15 MNHN AR 9166). 10 – 11, 14 – 15 epigyne (10, 14 ventral view; 11, 15 dorsal view); 12 – 13 left male palp (12 ventral view, 13 retrolateral view). 16 – 17 Drassodex simoni sp. nov. (MNHN ARM 034 a, holotype). 16 – 17 epigyne (16 ventral view, 17 dorsal view). 18 – 19 Drassodex aff. drescoi (MNHN AR 9167). 18 – 19 epigyne (18 ventral view, 19 dorsal view). (A = atrium; AA = anterior arch; B = bursa; CD = coiled duct; CO = copulatory opening; EC = embolar coil; FLS = flattened lanceolate structure; IP = inferior prong of the RTA; MA = median apophysis; MC = membranous coil; S = socket; SP = superior prong of the RTA)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/189209/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">
Fig. 
<number box="[1157,1187,229,255]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="18.0">18</number>
</figureCitation>
) rather than piriform (
<figureCitation box="[159,247,268,294]" captionStart="FIGURES 20 – 27. 20 – 23" captionStartId="15.[151,269,1890,1914]" captionTargetBox="[168,1417,204,1859]" captionTargetId="figure@15.[162,1424,194,1866]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURES 20 – 27. 20 – 23 Drassodex simoni sp. nov. (Ledoux collection, after Murphy 2007: figs p. 235). 20 – 21 epigyne (20 ventral view, 21 dorsal view); 22 – 23 left male palp (22 ventral view, 23 retrolateral view). 24 – 27 Drassodex drescoi sp. nov. (24 – 25 Dresco collection, MNHN AR 14598, holotype; 26 – 27 MNHN AR 9167). 24 – 25 epigyne (24 ventral view, 25 dorsal view); 26 – 27 left male palp (26 ventral view, 27 retrolateral view)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/189210/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">
Fig. 
<number box="[214,247,268,294]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="24.0">24</number>
</figureCitation>
); we have not found other differences in somatic or internal genitalic characters (
<figureCitation box="[1197,1287,268,294]" captionStart="FIGURES 10 – 19. 10 – 15" captionStartId="12.[151,269,1802,1826]" captionTargetBox="[171,1414,182,1782]" captionTargetId="figure@12.[160,1427,174,1786]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 10 – 19. 10 – 15 Drassodex heeri (Pavesi, 1873) (10 – 13 SMF 22517 / 3; 14 – 15 MNHN AR 9166). 10 – 11, 14 – 15 epigyne (10, 14 ventral view; 11, 15 dorsal view); 12 – 13 left male palp (12 ventral view, 13 retrolateral view). 16 – 17 Drassodex simoni sp. nov. (MNHN ARM 034 a, holotype). 16 – 17 epigyne (16 ventral view, 17 dorsal view). 18 – 19 Drassodex aff. drescoi (MNHN AR 9167). 18 – 19 epigyne (18 ventral view, 19 dorsal view). (A = atrium; AA = anterior arch; B = bursa; CD = coiled duct; CO = copulatory opening; EC = embolar coil; FLS = flattened lanceolate structure; IP = inferior prong of the RTA; MA = median apophysis; MC = membranous coil; S = socket; SP = superior prong of the RTA)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/189209/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Figs 19</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1300,1333,268,294]" captionStart="FIGURES 20 – 27. 20 – 23" captionStartId="15.[151,269,1890,1914]" captionTargetBox="[168,1417,204,1859]" captionTargetId="figure@15.[162,1424,194,1866]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURES 20 – 27. 20 – 23 Drassodex simoni sp. nov. (Ledoux collection, after Murphy 2007: figs p. 235). 20 – 21 epigyne (20 ventral view, 21 dorsal view); 22 – 23 left male palp (22 ventral view, 23 retrolateral view). 24 – 27 Drassodex drescoi sp. nov. (24 – 25 Dresco collection, MNHN AR 14598, holotype; 26 – 27 MNHN AR 9167). 24 – 25 epigyne (24 ventral view, 25 dorsal view); 26 – 27 left male palp (26 ventral view, 27 retrolateral view)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/189210/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">25</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="16.[151,1437,151,564]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">
Considering the other material examined, in particular the couples collected in and around the Parco Naturale Alpe Veglia-Devero, in 
<collectingCountry box="[566,634,345,371]" name="Italy" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Italia</collectingCountry>
, we did not have any doubt how to associate the males with the corresponding females belonging to the piriform-shaped 
<typeStatus box="[860,918,384,410]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">type</typeStatus>
. As the vial n° 
<collectionCode LSID="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34988" box="[1111,1204,384,410]" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34988" name="Museum National d'Histoire Naturelle" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">MNHN</collectionCode>
<collectionCode box="[1212,1254,384,410]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">AR</collectionCode>
<number box="[1263,1324,384,410]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="9167.0">9167</number>
contains specimens collected in at least three different localities, we cannot associate these three females as a morph of 
<taxonomicName box="[151,281,461,486]" class="Arachnida" family="Gnaphosidae" genus="Drassodex" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="drescoi">
<emphasis box="[151,281,461,486]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">D. drescoi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but at the same time we cannot consider them to be a separate species. We then decided to determine them as 
<taxonomicName box="[373,540,500,526]" class="Arachnida" family="Gnaphosidae" genus="Drassodex" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="drescoi">
<emphasis box="[373,401,500,525]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">D.</emphasis>
aff. 
<emphasis box="[455,540,500,525]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">drescoi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, while waiting for new material.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
